
                                <p>This week, the upcoming Symfony 7.4 version <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony/commit/74fc896a8e13930a27037f7c97c76ca353ae1a51">deprecated the XML configuration format</a> for services and routing, introduced <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony/commit/770dc405746b2bf680e560d685d8778df653cbc5">new attributes</a> to configure console arguments, <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony/commit/28fba8011187c44bb26771f6ff09f234949df735">deprecated the get() method</a> of the Request class, and improved the <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony/commit/9c413a356ccb3c982add8fa2b19813927157aa0e">caching HTTP client</a>.</p>

<h2>Symfony development highlights</h2>

<p>This week, 64 pull requests were merged (51 in code and 13 in docs) and 46 issues were closed (29 in code and 17 in docs). Excluding merges, 29 authors made additions and deletions. See details for <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony/pulse">code</a> and <a href="https://github.com/symfony/symfony-docs/pulse">docs</a>.</p>

